1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,011
Listen to these guides carefully, then make a conscious effort to practice them and build your confidence.

2
00:00:07,011 --> 00:00:08,771
1.

3
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:10,931
Be a front-seater.

4
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:19,011
Ever notice in meetings, in church, classrooms, and other kinds of assemblies, how the back seats fill up first?

5
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:24,771
Most folks scramble to sit in the back rows so they won't be too conspicuous.

6
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:30,130
And the reason they are afraid to be conspicuous is that they lack confidence.

7
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:33,011
Sitting up front builds confidence.

8
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,130
Practice it.

9
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:38,771
From now on, make it a rule to sit as close to the front as you can.

10
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:46,931
Sure, you may be a little more conspicuous in the front, but remember, there is nothing inconspicuous about success.

11
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,090
Two, practice making eye contact.

12
00:00:51,281 --> 00:00:55,011
How a person uses his eyes tells us a lot about him.

13
00:00:55,120 --> 00:01:00,690
Instinctively, you ask yourself questions about the fellow who doesn't look you in the eye.

14
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:02,451
What's he trying to hide?

15
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:03,891
What's he afraid of?

16
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,371
Is he trying to put something over on me?

17
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:08,371
Is he holding something back?

18
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:13,251
Usually, failure to make eye contact says one of two things.

19
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:16,690
It may say, I feel weak beside you.

20
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,610
I feel inferior to you.

21
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,210
I'm afraid of you.

22
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:25,090
or avoiding another person's eyes may say, I feel guilty.

23
00:01:25,201 --> 00:01:29,251
I've done something or I thought something that I don't want you to know.

24
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:34,210
I'm afraid if I let my eyes connect with yours, you'll see through me.

25
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:39,170
You say nothing good about yourself when you avoid making eye contact.

26
00:01:39,281 --> 00:01:41,331
You say, I'm afraid.

27
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,170
I lack confidence.

28
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:48,451
Conquer this fear by making yourself look the other person in the eyes.

29
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:53,731
Looking the other person in the eye tells him, I'm honest and above board.

30
00:01:53,761 --> 00:01:55,650
I believe in what I'm telling you.

31
00:01:55,681 --> 00:01:56,851
I'm not afraid.

32
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,130
I'm confident.

33
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,610
Make your eyes work for you.

34
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:03,170
Aim them right at the other person's eyes.

35
00:02:03,281 --> 00:02:07,650
It not only gives you confidence, it wins you confidence too.

